- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper addresses the problem of autonomous navigation, which is a key area of robotics research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses recurrent neural networks for lane identification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper proposes an AI-based solution for lane identification. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve natural language processing in the form of text-based lane identification.
